Minister of basic education Angie Motshekga revealed on Tuesday afternoon that the department has decided to include the Hash Tag or word #FeesMustFall in new Enlgish, Zulu and Xhosa dictionaries.&#8220;This decision came after long discussions me and the minister of higher education had with students protesting for fees to fall. After talking to these students and seeing their enthusiasm, we got to like the word ourselves, in fact we loved it. #FeesMustFall.&#8221; said Motshekga.&#8220;I can&#8217;t believe I didn&#8217;t understand all of this from the beginning. Now I&#8217;m going to get a couple of t-shirts and brand them #FeesMustFall.Actually, we have concluded that the word #FeesMustFall be put in every English, Zulu, and Xhosa dictionaries as of next year. It is part of the South African heritage now.&#8221;continued Motshekga.&nbsp;